burlap.shell.command

Interface ShellCommand

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AddRelationCommand, AddRelationSGCommand, AddStateObjectCommand, AddStateObjectSGCommand, AliasCommand, AliasesCommand, CommandsCommand, EpisodeRecordingCommands.EpisodeBrowserCommand, EpisodeRecordingCommands.RecordCommand, ExecuteActionCommand, GameCommand, GenerateStateCommand, HelpCommand, IsTerminalCommand, IsTerminalSGCommand, JointActionCommand, LastJointActionCommand, ManualAgentsCommands.ListManualAgents, ManualAgentsCommands.LSManualAgentActionsCommands, ManualAgentsCommands.RegisterAgentCommand, ManualAgentsCommands.SetAgentAction, ObservationCommand, QuitCommand, RemoveRelationCommand, RemoveRelationSGCommand, RemoveStateObjectCommand, RemoveStateObjectSGCommand, ResetEnvCommand, RewardCommand, RewardsCommand, SetAttributeCommand, SetAttributeSGCommand, VisualExplorer.LivePollCommand, WorldObservationCommand

    public interface ShellCommand
    An interface for implementing shell commands. Requires implementing a default name for the command and a call command for what should be executed when the command is called. When executed, commands return a return code. -1 indicates a parsing error. 0 indicates standard completion. 1 indicates that an important external variable, such as the state of an Environment was changed.
    Author:
    James MacGlashan.
